Subject: [PATCH] T2.6: Extract route table into declarative data module
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Refactors App.jsx's role-gated routes from four duplicated JSX blocks
into a declarative table driven by role filters.

Before:
  Four per-role JSX blocks (admin/tc/investor/pml) each declared 8-11
  <Route> entries. Heavy duplication: /tc-directory, /investor-directory,
  /pml-directory, /messages, /support etc. repeated across 3-4 blocks.
  Permission matrix only readable by scanning all four blocks side by
  side. Adding a new route to all roles required touching the same
  JSX in multiple places.

After:
  src/lib/routes.jsx exports AUTHENTICATED_ROUTES as a single ordered
  array of { path, roles, element } entries. Shared routes use a roles
  array with multiple values; /profile entries (which resolve to
  different components per role) are listed once per role with the
  same path but different element.

  App.jsx renders userRoutes = routesForRole(user.role) as a simple
  .map() inside the Layout <Route>. One canonical source of truth for
  the permission matrix.

Line counts:
  src/App.jsx      180 -> 107 lines (-40%)
  src/lib/routes.jsx  +105 lines (new)

Behavior preservation (verified before committing):
Extracted each role's original route list from App.jsx and diffed
against what routesForRole() returns for that role. All four roles
match EXACTLY — admin, tc, investor, pml. No routes added, removed,
or had their role access changed.

Pre-existing quirks preserved as-is (flagged in routes.jsx comments):
  - TC can access /profile/pml but not /profile/tc
  - Admin has /profile/tc and /profile/pml but not /profile/investor
These are preserved because the goal is a pure refactor, not a
behavior change. Worth revisiting as a separate product decision.

Files:
  - src/App.jsx      (180 -> 107 lines)
  - src/lib/routes.jsx  (new, 105 lines)

Verification:
  - npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
  - npm run build: succeeds
  - Route parity: all 4 roles match exactly between old and new
    implementation (verified via Python diff script)
